dataIdInfo.idAbs: This polygon data layer represents buildings for Brown County, Wisconsin in 2010. It is a feature class within the geodatabase, Brown_Buildings_2010.gdb.[Building footprint data was mapped out using aerial orthophotography by the aerial photo contractor as part of the project (but this option was paid for by interested municipalities). Brown County does not maintain or update building footprint data. In 2000, these municipalities included the City of Green Bay and the Village of Suamico. In 2010, several more communities opted to have building footprints created. Because of the various years of data, each building feature is coded with a "DateCaptured" field.]
dataIdInfo.idPurp:
This layer is intended for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data.
[The purpose of the Building layer is to map out the building footprint to show the size and shape of buildings. This data is used for various applications such as computing the impervious surface on parcels, and for general cartography.]
